1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,200
DETECTIVE: Thanks for coming in, Mr. Hale. Just routine.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:07,800
HALE: You said on the phone it was about the Briar Park case.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,200
DETECTIVE: That's right. Do you know why we're talking to you?

4
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:14,800
HALE: Because I live two blocks from the park. Like a lot of people.

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,500
DETECTIVE: A woman was found there last Sunday. Margaret Vale.

6
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:21,000
HALE: I read about it in the paper.

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:24,500
DETECTIVE: We pulled traffic cam footage from Briar and Eleventh.

8
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:28,000
DETECTIVE: Your car passes that intersection at 6:42 a.m.

9
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:31,500
HALE: I jog in that area. That's not new information.

10
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:35,200
DETECTIVE: Mr. Hale, you don't jog. You drove.

11
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,500
HALE: Sometimes I drive to the trailhead and then I jog.

12
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:42,000
DETECTIVE: At 6:42 a.m. on a Sunday. Same time she died.

13
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:45,000
HALE: I didn't know what time she died. The paper didn't say.

14
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:48,500
DETECTIVE: That's because we never released the time.

15
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
HALE: I — I assumed. People assume things.

16
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,800
DETECTIVE: Did you know Margaret Vale, Mr. Hale?

17
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,500
HALE: No. I told the officer outside that already.

18
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:04,000
DETECTIVE: Then can you explain this photograph?

19
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,800
DETECTIVE: It was on her phone. Taken six weeks ago. You and her.

20
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:12,000
HALE: That's — that's a community fundraiser.

21
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:15,500
HALE: We were both there. Doesn't mean we knew each other.

22
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:19,000
DETECTIVE: She had your number written on the back of the print.

23
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:23,500
HALE: I want a lawyer.

24
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:27,000
DETECTIVE: That's your right. Before you make that call,

25
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:30,000
DETECTIVE: I need to tell you something we found.

26
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:33,500
DETECTIVE: There was a letter in her apartment.

27
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,800
DETECTIVE: It was addressed to her brother.

28
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:41,000
DETECTIVE: She had been looking for him for thirty-one years.

29
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:45,000
DETECTIVE: She found him last spring. We pulled DNA from a coffee cup.

30
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,800
HALE: I don't — I don't understand.

31
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,500
DETECTIVE: Mr. Hale, did your mother put you up for adoption in 1992?

32
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,500
HALE: How did you —

33
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,500
DETECTIVE: She wrote you a letter. Margaret. Your sister.

34
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,000
DETECTIVE: She wanted to meet you. Properly. Last Sunday.

35
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:08,000
DETECTIVE: At 6:30 a.m. At the trailhead.

36
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:11,000
HALE: I didn't — I didn't know.

37
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,000
DETECTIVE: Didn't know what, Mr. Hale?

38
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:17,500
HALE: I went there. I went there to meet her.

39
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,000
HALE: She wasn't there. There was a man.

40
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:24,500
HALE: He was leaving. He had a bag. I didn't see his face.

41
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:27,000
DETECTIVE: A man was leaving the trailhead at 6:42.

42
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:30,000
DETECTIVE: And you didn't think to mention this to anyone?

43
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:33,500
HALE: I — I didn't know who she was. To me.

44
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:37,000
HALE: I drove home. I told myself it was nothing.

45
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:41,000
DETECTIVE: Mr. Hale, can you describe the man you saw?

46
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:44,500
HALE: Tall. Limping. He was limping on his left side.

47
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
DETECTIVE: One more question. The lawyer can wait.

48
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,500
DETECTIVE: When did you find out she was your sister?

49
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,500
HALE: Two minutes ago. Just now.

50
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
HALE: She just wanted to meet me. And I left.

51
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:02,500
DETECTIVE: Mr. Hale, I'm going to need you to stay.

52
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:06,000
DETECTIVE: Not as a suspect. As the only witness we have.
